    "what_description": "Epacris tasmanica is an evergreen shrub native to Tasmania, Australia, and southeastern New South Wales. It belongs to the family Ericaceae, which comprises heath and heather plants. The plant grows up to 1-2 meters in height, with a spread of 1-1.5 meters, and has a compact, rounded habit. Its leaves are linear, lanceolate, and entire, measuring 10-25 mm in length, with a green color on top and a hairy, white underside. The plant produces small, white, bell-shaped flowers in clusters, which are highly fragrant and appear from September to November.",
